    <a href="/content/ryerson/calendar/2020-2021/courses/social-work/SWP/51AB.html" title="SWP 51A/B - Field Practicum" class="courseListCourseLink"><span class="courseListCourseCode">SWP 51A/B</span> - <span class="courseListCourseName">Field Practicum</span></a>
    
	
		<div class="courseListDescription"><p>The second practicum emphasizes students learning in the field about themselves and social work practice through: developing critical self-reflexivity in working with people and transformative activities; engaging in anti-oppressive support and change processes; understanding links between policy, research and practice and how these are influenced by social, economic, political and organizational contexts; understanding professional roles and values and ethics of social work. Students are in field placement three days a week for two semesters.</p>
