		<div class="courseListDescription">This course will explore the impact of social policies on aging populations. A Canadian perspective will be taken. The significance of changing Canadian demographic factors for social planning will be analyzed and the special needs of the elderly, relative to retirement, income maintenance and leisure will be explored in the context of the social process of aging.</div>
	
	
		<div class="courseListLength"><span class="courseInfoLabels">Weekly Contact: </span><span class="courseInfoValues">Lecture: 3 hrs. </span></div>
	
	
