		<div class="courseListDescription">This course reviews social work approaches to human rights and analyzes issues, concepts, policies, and legal and institutional structures associated with equity and human rights in Canada aimed at forwarding social work practice. The course will incorporate reference to the circumstances of Indigenous Peoples and other marginalized groups from a human rights perspective.</div>
	
	
